# ğŸš€ Automated Server Health Monitor (Linux | Cron | Bash)

## ğŸ“Œ Project Overview

In real production environments, engineers do not manually log in to servers to check CPU, memory, disk usage, or service health.

Monitoring must be:

- Automated
- Continuous
- Alert-driven

This project simulates a real-world DevOps/SRE scenario by building a **Server Health Monitoring & Alerting system using Bash and Cron**.

It automatically checks:

- Disk usage
- CPU usage
- Memory usage
- Service status

and generates alerts in a log file when thresholds are crossed.

---

## ğŸ¯ Objective

To design a lightweight monitoring solution that:

- Runs automatically
- Detects system resource issues
- Logs alerts with clear messages
- Mimics real production monitoring behaviour

---

## ğŸ›  Tech Stack

- Linux (Ubuntu / WSL)
- Bash scripting
- Cron (job scheduler)
- System monitoring commands

