## âš™ï¸ How It Works

### 1ï¸âƒ£ Script Execution

The script collects system metrics using:

- `df` â†’ Disk usage
- `top` â†’ CPU usage
- `free` â†’ Memory usage
- `systemctl` â†’ Service health

### 2ï¸âƒ£ Threshold Check

Each resource is compared against a predefined limit.

Example:

- Disk > 90%

If the threshold is crossed â†’ an alert is generated.

---

### 3ï¸âƒ£ Alert Logging

Alerts are written to:


#health.log


This simulates how monitoring tools send:

- Logs
- Notifications
- Alerts

in production systems.

---

### 4ï¸âƒ£ Full Automation with Cron

The script is scheduled using:

crontab -e

Runs automatically every minute:
# hr min day mont weekdays
/home/rolex/server-health-monitor/monitor.sh


This removes manual health checks completely.

---

## ğŸ§ª Alert Testing (Production-Style Validation)

Instead of actually filling the disk (unsafe in real systems), alert testing was performed by:

- Temporarily lowering threshold values
- Running the script
- Verifying alert generation in real time

This follows the **same safe alert validation strategy used in production environments**.

